1 (5 oz) cans Bumble Bee® Solid White Albacore Tuna, drained
1 avocado, mashed
2 tablespoons Sriracha sauce
1 tablespoon Dijon mustard
2-3 tablespoons green onions, chopped
2 tablespoons mayonnaise, divided
2 tablespoons red bell pepper, finely chopped
1 tablespoon fresh cilantro, finely chopped
1 teaspoon fresh ginger, finely minced
Salt and black pepper to taste
2 limes, juiced
1/2 cup grated cheddar cheese, divided
2 tablespoons fresh cilantro, chopped for garnish (optional)
4 (10 inch) flour tortillas or wraps
LEEK BEANS:
In a medium bowl, combine the tuna with the avocado, Sriracha sauce, Dijon mustard, green onions, 1 tablespoon mayonnaise and red bell pepper. Mix well. Season with salt and black pepper. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining tablespoon of mayonnaise with lime juice and grated cheese. Add more salt and black pepper if desired. Set aside.
Lay one tortilla or wrap flat on a clean work surface. Spread the tuna mixture evenly on the tortilla. Fold in half to create a half-moon shape. Carefully transfer the tortilla to a baking sheet and repeat with remaining tortillas or wraps.
Bake in a preheated 400F oven for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown and crispy on the outside. Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve with leek beans on the side.
